The entmax transformation is defined as:

\[ \text{entmax}(z) = \begin{cases} 
\exp(z_i - \max_j \exp(z_j)) & \text{if } z_i = \max_j z_j \\
0 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases} \]

where \( z \) is a vector of real numbers and \( z_i \) denotes the \( i \)-th element of the vector \( z \).
